defaultThe DfE has an “Academies Group” which oversees all aspects of conversion of schools to academies.
default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTKAT does not market 
defaultitself 
defaultand has grown in two ways.  Firstly, by schools approaching TKAT directly and secondly, by the “B
defaultr
defaultokerage Division” of the DfE working with schools/LAs to recommend TKAT as a sponsor.  Most of TKAT’s academies have come through brokerage ie the governing body of the school has been “guided” by the DfE/LA to choose  TKAT.  This is a great improvement on the previous practice of “beauty parades” whereby
default a number of sponsors present
default to a governing body 
defaultwith the governing body clearly tempted to choose
default the one least likely to cause much change. 
default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAll schools that are to become an academy have a “lead contact” at the DfE and this works well.  If a school that wants to become an academy is PFI the whole process of conversion is slowed dramatically.  I believe we are the only non-secular chain to have a Church School.  This was a long process and my understanding is that this is going to be a rare occurrence, if it happens at all.  The Diocese has to give approval and this is now being withheld.
default2.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
