default&#xa0;default3.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCurrently, the Secretary of State monitors the progress of academies 
defaultthrough national data; DfE official and adviser visits and Ofsted reports.  When an academy has not made accelerated progress over a period of time (often a year) then a pre-warning notice is served.
default3.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFrom our experience it appears that the DfE and Ofsted do not work together or coordinate their work.  For example, an academy can go into special measures and not be given a pre-war
defaultning notice yet 
default schools
default, not in category, 
