default5.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthere is more accountablitiy now
default than there ever was under the LA.  Each 
defaultTKAT academy is accountable to its
default governing body.  Each governing body has the right skill set and has had appropriate training. The governing body is accountable to the TKAT Board, which analyses data regularly on all its academies.  This ensures that there are no surprises and that any intervention is brought in at an early stage.
default5.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn addition, TKAT is accountable to the LA, DfE and Ofsted.
default5.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGovernance has been an issue at all levels.  In October 2012 TKAT commissioned Deloittes’ to carry out a review of the company and suggest the models of governance needed.  We have implemented their recommendations which could be a template for other academy chains. Our model of a small (7) but highly qualified Board, with an Executive Chairman
default,
default is central to our model of governance.  We have separated out the strategic lead of the company, through the Board and the operational side, led by the CEO.
default5.5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe have two sub-committees: Audit &amp; Risk chaired by a non-executive director, who has 20 years experience with J P Morgan, and a Remuneration &amp; Nomination Committee which reviews the salaries and performance of senior executives as well as well as agreeing a shadow structure as part of succession planning.  Audit &amp; Risk monitor the finance but also monitor risk.  The Corporate Risk Register is owned by the A&amp;R committee, with only the top 6 risks being taken to the Board.  There is a process of escalation of risk from the initial due diligence carried out on any school wishing to become a TKAT academy through the school risk register to the corporate risk register.  There is a clearly defined escalation process for risk .
default  We believe that this is a more business-like approach than might be seen anywhere else in the academy chain world.
default&#xa0;
default5.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAt academy level we have taken an approach to governance depending on need. For example in, Thanet and Chichester where governance needed to be strengthened we have set up regional boards with clearly defined terms of reference, focusing on holding the academies to account.  These Regional Boards have a strong Chairman, who may not be from the area.
default5.7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe are rolling this model of governance out to our schools in Hampshire and Crawley.  
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;default6.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAcademy status is appropriate for clusters of primary schools, a single small primary school joining a secondary academy trust or a large primary school on its own.
default6.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMany, possibly most
default,
default primary schools have a dependency culture on the LA. In some cases this may have been actively encouraged by the LA.  In the majority of cases the finance/business manager in a primary school would not have the skills required to manage the audit and finance function in an academy.  They are often part-time and not qualified for the role. This means that either a comprehensive and intense training programme needs to be put in place or a “Finance Director” with the required skills is appointed across a number of primary schools.
default6.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere are major savings to be made through having a comprehensive procurement policy for all the academies.  TKAT’s is currently in draft form. Many of our academies do not have the experience or expertise in negotiating “value for money” contracts. This expertise lies at the centre of TKAT through the Chief Finance Officer.  However, there are already examples where we have made savings for our academies, which releases funding to be reinvested 
defaultby the academies 
defaultin the core business of teaching and learning.
default6.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWebsitesdefault defaultThe cost of an average website with the latest functionality is around 5-10k each.
default&#xa0;
default TKAT has negotiated a cost of 2.5k for each of our academies websites which is funded centrally and offered to all our academies as a zero cost.
default&#xa0;
default6.5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLicensingdefault defaultTKAT hold a central Microsoft Licence Agreement.
default&#xa0;
default Each of our academies are encouraged to join our licencing programme as they will achieve better pricing than through many of their usual resellers.
default&#xa0;
default We estimate that across 25 academies, we have saved around 10-15k on licensing costs. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultIn addition, all full time staff at each of the academies signed up to our licensing programmes are entitled to a free copy of Microsoft Office, (worth around £100 per person).
default6.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultProcurementdefault 
defaultWhen procuring hardware we encourage academies to use our preferred procurement channel, ESPO (Eastern Shires Procurement Organisation).
default&#xa0;
default This organisation has more than thirty years of experience in offering a centralised procurement service and can provide TKAT with assurance of compliance with the EU Procurement Directive. It is also worth noting that ESPO is run on a not for profit basis.
default&#xa0;
default As ESPO have pre-negotiated contracts with the large computer manufacturers such as Dell, HP and Lenovo they are able to provide our academies with pricing that simply wouldn’t be available through an everyday reseller.
default&#xa0;
default During the summer of this year, an academy obtained 3 quotes for an identical spec computer through the normal suppliers they use.
default&#xa0;
default We (TKAT) requested a quote from ESPO/Dell who came in just under £80 cheaper per unit.
default&#xa0;
default Based on a collective total of 500 pcs, this saving equated to around 40k.
